  <fr:frontmatter>
    <fr:anchor>1314</fr:anchor>
    <fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-2.2.6</fr:addr>
    <fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-2.2.6.xml</fr:route>
    <fr:authors />
    <fr:number>2.2.6</fr:number>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a non-singular projective variety of pure dimension <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>.
    A choice of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex> defines an orientation of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and an isomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z}(1)\simeq \mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>.
    The corresponding trace morphism
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       \operatorname {H}^{2n}(X,\mathbb {Z}(n)) \to  \mathbb {Z}     ]]></fr:tex>
    that is induced does not depend on the choice of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>By Hodge, for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\leqslant  n]]></fr:tex>, the morphism
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       L^{n-i}       = -\wedge  c''_1(\mathcal {O}(1))^{n-i}\colon        \operatorname {H}^i(X,\mathbb {Z}) \to  \operatorname {H}^{2n-i}(X,\mathbb {Z}(n-i))     ]]></fr:tex>
    is an isomorphism, and, combined with Poincaré duality
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       \operatorname {H}^i(X,\mathbb {Z})\otimes \operatorname {H}^{2n-i}(X,\mathbb {Z}(n-i))       \to  \operatorname {H}^{2n}(X,\mathbb {Z}(n-i))       \to  \mathbb {Z}(-i)     ]]></fr:tex>
    gives a polarisation on the <fr:em>primitive part</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Ker}(L^{n-i+1})]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^i(X,\mathbb {Z})]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>We thus deduce that the rational Hodge structures <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^i(X,\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex> are polarisable.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
